    {
      "page_number": 1,
      "raw_text": "There are more cattlemen at the\nInterstate fair this year than horse\nmen, TO judge by the great interest\ndisplayed in their stock. All avail\nable space has been taken up.\n\n\nThe most attention is given to\nthe 35 headof Red Polled belonging\nto Cogswell & Miller. This firm\ncarried off the sweepstakes at the\nPortland for any aged cattle and\ntheir bull was declared grand cham.\npion. On the Pacific Northwest\nfair circuit last year they cap\ntured 73 prizes.\n\n\nThere are many other fine cat\ntie exhibits. Judging and awarding\nof prizes will be done by Professors\nE. Z. Elliot, of Pullman. Wash,\nand French, of Moscow, Idaho."
    }
